<h1 class="page-heading">Technologies used by this site</h1>

<p>This website is a blog application built with the <a href="http://gaelyk.appspot.com">Gaelyk</a> lightweight toolkit for <a href="http://code.google.com/appengine">Google App Engine</a>, and using the <a href="http://groovy.codehaus.org">Groovy</a> dynamic language for the JVM. It's a clone of the <a href="https://github.com/glaforge/bloogaey">Bloogaey</a> application originally developed by <a href="http://glaforge.appspot.com/">Guillaume Laforge</a></p>

<p>The highlighting of the code samples is done thanks to <a href="http://softwaremaniacs.org/soft/highlight/en/">highlight.js</a> and the ajax bits are powered by <a href="http://jquery.com/">jQuery</a>.</p>

<p>The <a href="http://templates.arcsin.se/">template</a> for this blog is coming from <a href="http://arcsin.se/">Arcsin</a>.</p>

<p>The <a href="/social">social</a> page is harvesting my Twitter timeline.</p>

<p>For sharing purpose, <a href="http://sharethis.com/">ShareThis</a> provides the sharing capabilities with the external world and <a href="http://intensedebate.com/">IntenseDebate</a> provides the commenting system.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.google.com/cse/">Google Custom Search</a> takes care of the search page.</p>

<p>You can find the <a href="https://github.com/erdi/bloogaey">sources of this website</a> on GitHub.</p>